text: Bill Bailey is a true Nebraska hero. I am honored to tell his story. #NEHeroes #ProudNebraskan
name: Deb Fischer

text: Bill was a wonderful husband, brother, son, father. He dedicated quite a bit of his life to helping other people. #NEHeroes
name: Deb Fischer

text: Specialist Bailey earned several military awards including the Purple Heart, Bronze Star, Iraqi Campaign Medal & Combat Action Badge. #Honor
name: Deb Fischer

text: More than one thousand people gathered in Bellevue to remember Bill. #NEHeroes
name: Deb Fischer

text: On May 25, 2007, during a security escort mission, Bill’s vehicle struck an improvised explosive device. Bill Bailey was killed. #NEHeroes
name: Deb Fischer

text: By 2007, the insurgency in Iraq had erupted to new levels of violence. Increased American forces sought to destroy the al Qaeda network.
name: Deb Fischer

text: In 2006, his unit was deployed and assigned to provide security escorts for truck convoys operating out of Balad Air Base in #Iraq.
name: Deb Fischer

text: That deep desire to serve the country continued to tug at him. In 2005, Bill re-enlisted in the @NENationalGuard #Courage
name: Deb Fischer

text: Bill’s protective nature made him a great father. It also made him a great firefighter. #NeHeroes
name: Deb Fischer

text: After 9/11, Bill felt the call to serve his country again. But, first things first. Bill and Dee married in 2004.
name: Deb Fischer

text: In December 2000, Bill met Dee. She was a bank teller at Wells Fargo; he drove an armored truck. They met through a service window.
name: Deb Fischer

text: Bill attended Bellevue East where the call to protect his country prompted him to enlist in the @NENationalGuard in 1995.
name: Deb Fischer
